# Real Time Clock(RTC) Display

## Project Submission

### Student Details
- **Name:** Monitha
- **Domain:** Embedded Systems and IoT

### Project Overview
The RTC Display Alarm Clock is an embedded systems project that displays real-time time on a 4-digit 7-segment display. Users can set and modify the current time, configure alarms, and use snooze functionality. The system generates an audible alarm when the set alarm time is reached.

### Features
- Real-Time Clock (RTC) Display
- Time Adjustment using Buttons
- Alarm Enable/Disable
- Alarm Time Setting
- Snooze Functionality
- Audible Alarm Notification

### Components Used
- ESP32 / Arduino Board
- RTC Module (DS1307/DS3231)
- 4-Digit 7-Segment Display
- Push Buttons
- Buzzer/Speaker
- Jumper Wires

### Project Output
The system continuously displays the current time and activates an alarm at the configured time, providing a simple and effective digital alarm clock solution.

